title: Morgan, Saints Get UMAC Win over 'Jackets
text:
Morgan, Saints Get UMAC Win over 'Jackets 
By Zach Schneider October 15, 2015 Updated Oct 15, 2015 at 9:53 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- Sean Morgan scored two first half goals on Thursday night as he and the St. Scholastica men's soccer team earned a 3-1 win over UW-Superior, marking the Saints' second win this season over their Twin Ports rival. 
Morgan's first goal came just five minutes into the match and was followed 10 minutes later by a tally from Shawayne Folkes. Both players also scored first half goals in the first meeting of the season. 
Morgan's second came just minutes before halftime, making the lead 3-0 at the break. Joey Gustafson scored in the second half for UW-Superior, but that was as close as the visitors got. 
St. Scholastica is now (12-2-0) overall this season, while UW-Superior is (11-4-0).
